{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So, what I'm going to do is"},{"time":2000,"text":"just give you the latest episode of India's --"},{"time":4000,"text":"maybe the world's -- longest running soap opera,"},{"time":7000,"text":"which is cricket."},{"time":9000,"text":"And may it run forever, because it gives people like me a living."},{"time":12000,"text":"It's got everything that you'd want a normal soap opera to want:"},{"time":17000,"text":"It's got love, joy, happiness,"},{"time":19000,"text":"sadness, tears, laughter,"},{"time":21000,"text":"lots of deceit, intrigue."},{"time":23000,"text":"And like all good soaps, it jumps 20 years"},{"time":25000,"text":"when the audience interest changes."},{"time":27000,"text":"And that's exactly what cricket has done."},{"time":29000,"text":"It's jumped 20 years"},{"time":31000,"text":"into 20-over game."},{"time":33000,"text":"And that's what I'm going to talk about,"},{"time":35000,"text":"how a small change"},{"time":37000,"text":"leads to a very big revolution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39000,"text":"But it wasn't always like that."},{"time":41000,"text":"Cricket wasn't always this"},{"time":43000,"text":"speed-driven generations game."},{"time":45000,"text":"There was a time when you played cricket,"},{"time":47000,"text":"you played timeless test matches,"},{"time":49000,"text":"when you played on till the game got over."},{"time":52000,"text":"And there was this game in March 1939"},{"time":55000,"text":"that started on the third of March"},{"time":57000,"text":"and ended on the 14th of March."},{"time":59000,"text":"And it only ended because the English cricketers"},{"time":62000,"text":"had to go from Durban to Cape Town,"},{"time":64000,"text":"which is a two-hour train journey,"},{"time":66000,"text":"to catch the ship that left on the 17th,"},{"time":69000,"text":"because the next ship wasn't around for a long time."},{"time":71000,"text":"So, the match was ended in between."},{"time":74000,"text":"And one of the English batsmen said, \"You know what?"},{"time":76000,"text":"Another half an hour and we would have won.\""},{"time":78000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":81000,"text":"Another half an hour after 12 days."},{"time":83000,"text":"There were two Sundays in between. But of course, Sundays are church days,"},{"time":87000,"text":"so you don't play on Sundays. And one day it rained,"},{"time":89000,"text":"so they all sat around making friends with each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":91000,"text":"But there is a reason why India fell in love with cricket:"},{"time":93000,"text":"because we had about the same pace of life."},{"time":97000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":99000,"text":"The Mahabharata was like that as well, wasn't it?"},{"time":101000,"text":"You fought by day, then it was sunset,"},{"time":106000,"text":"so everyone went back home."},{"time":108000,"text":"And then you worked out your strategy,"},{"time":110000,"text":"and you came and fought the next day, and you went back home again."},{"time":113000,"text":"The only difference between the Mahabharata and our cricket was"},{"time":115000,"text":"that in cricket, everybody was alive to come back and fight the next day."},{"time":118000,"text":"Princes patronize the game,"},{"time":120000,"text":"not because they love the game,"},{"time":122000,"text":"but because it was a means of ingratiating themselves"},{"time":124000,"text":"to the British rulers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":126000,"text":"But there is one other reason why India fell in love with cricket,"},{"time":128000,"text":"which was, all you needed was a plank of wood"},{"time":130000,"text":"and a rubber ball, and any number of people"},{"time":132000,"text":"could play it anywhere."},{"time":134000,"text":"Take a look:"},{"time":136000,"text":"You could play it in the dump"},{"time":138000,"text":"with some rocks over there,"},{"time":141000,"text":"you could play it in a little alley --"},{"time":143000,"text":"you couldn't hit square anywhere, because the bat hit the wall;"},{"time":145000,"text":"don't forget the air conditioning and the cable wires."},{"time":147000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":148000,"text":"You could play it on the banks of the Ganges --"},{"time":151000,"text":"that's as clean as the Ganges has been for a long time."},{"time":153000,"text":"Or you could play many games in one small patch of land,"},{"time":155000,"text":"even if you didn't know which game you were actually in."},{"time":157000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":160000,"text":"As you can see, you can play anywhere."},{"time":162000,"text":"But slowly the game moved on,"},{"time":164000,"text":"you know, finally."}]},{"cues":[{"time":166000,"text":"You don't always have five days. So, we moved on,"},{"time":168000,"text":"and we started playing 50-over cricket."},{"time":170000,"text":"And then an enormous accident took place."},{"time":173000,"text":"In Indian sport we don't make things happen,"},{"time":175000,"text":"accidents happen and we're in the right place at the right time, sometimes."},{"time":178000,"text":"And we won this World Cup in 1983."},{"time":181000,"text":"And suddenly we fell in love with the 50-over game,"},{"time":184000,"text":"and we played it virtually every day."},{"time":186000,"text":"There was more 50-over cricket than anywhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":188000,"text":"But there was another big date."},{"time":190000,"text":"1983 was when we won the World Cup."},{"time":193000,"text":"1991,'92, we found a finance minister"},{"time":195000,"text":"and a prime minister"},{"time":197000,"text":"willing to let the world look at India,"},{"time":199000,"text":"rather than be this great country of intrigue"},{"time":201000,"text":"and mystery in this closed country."},{"time":203000,"text":"And so we allowed multinationals into India."},{"time":206000,"text":"We cut customs duties, we reduced import duties,"},{"time":208000,"text":"and we got all the multinationals coming in,"},{"time":210000,"text":"with multinational budgets,"},{"time":212000,"text":"who looked at per-capita income"},{"time":214000,"text":"and got very excited about the possibilities in India,"},{"time":217000,"text":"and were looking for a vehicle to reach every Indian."}]},{"cues":[{"time":220000,"text":"And there are only two vehicles in India -- one real, one scripted."},{"time":223000,"text":"The scripted one is what you see in the movies,"},{"time":225000,"text":"the real one was cricket."},{"time":226000,"text":"And so one of my friends sitting right here in front of me,"},{"time":228000,"text":"Ravi Dhariwal from Pepsi, decided he's going to take it"},{"time":231000,"text":"all over the world."},{"time":233000,"text":"And Pepsi was this big revolution, because they started taking cricket all over."},{"time":236000,"text":"And so cricket started becoming big;"},{"time":238000,"text":"cricket started bringing riches in."},{"time":240000,"text":"Television started covering cricket. For a long time"},{"time":242000,"text":"television said, \"We won't cover cricket"},{"time":244000,"text":"unless you pay us to cover it.\""},{"time":246000,"text":"Then they said, \"OK,"},{"time":248000,"text":"the next rights are sold for 55 million dollars."},{"time":250000,"text":"The next rights are sold for 612 million dollars.\""},{"time":252000,"text":"So, it's a bit of a curve, that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":255000,"text":"And then another big accident happened in our cricket."},{"time":258000,"text":"England invented 20 overs cricket,"},{"time":260000,"text":"and said, \"The world must play 20 overs cricket.\""},{"time":262000,"text":"Just as England invented cricket, and made the rest of the world play it."},{"time":265000,"text":"Thank God for them."},{"time":267000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":268000,"text":"And so, India had to go and play the T20 World Cup, you see."},{"time":271000,"text":"India didn't want to play the T20 World Cup."},{"time":274000,"text":"But we were forced to play it by an 8-1 margin."},{"time":276000,"text":"And then something very dramatic happened."},{"time":278000,"text":"We got to the final, and then this moment,"},{"time":280000,"text":"that will remain enshrined forever,"},{"time":282000,"text":"for everybody, take a look."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284000,"text":"(Crowd cheering)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":287000,"text":"The Pakistani batsman trying to clear the fielder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":289000,"text":"Announcer: And Zishan takes it! India wins!"},{"time":291000,"text":"What a match for a Twenty20 final."},{"time":294000,"text":"India, the world champions."},{"time":296000,"text":"(Cheering)"},{"time":297000,"text":"India, T20 champions."},{"time":300000,"text":"But what a game we had, M. S. Dhoni"},{"time":303000,"text":"got it right in the air, but Misbah-ul-Haq, what a player."},{"time":306000,"text":"A massive, massive success:"},{"time":308000,"text":"India, the world TT champions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314000,"text":"Harsha Bhogle: Suddenly India discovered this power of 20-overs cricket."},{"time":318000,"text":"The accident, of course, there, was that the batsman"},{"time":320000,"text":"thought the bowler was bowling fast."},{"time":322000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":323000,"text":"If he had bowled fast, the ball would have gone where it was meant to go,"},{"time":325000,"text":"but it didn't go. And we suddenly discovered"},{"time":328000,"text":"that we could be good at this game."},{"time":330000,"text":"And what it also did was"},{"time":332000,"text":"it led to a certain pride in the fact that India could be the best in the world."},{"time":335000,"text":"It was at a time when investment was coming in,"},{"time":337000,"text":"India was feeling a little more confident about itself."},{"time":339000,"text":"And so there was a feeling that there was great pride"},{"time":342000,"text":"in what we can do."},{"time":344000,"text":"And thankfully for all of us,"},{"time":346000,"text":"the English are very good at inventing things,"},{"time":348000,"text":"and then the gracious people that they are,"},{"time":350000,"text":"they let the world become very good at it."},{"time":352000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":354000,"text":"And so England invented T20 cricket,"},{"time":359000,"text":"and allowed India to hijack it."},{"time":361000,"text":"It was not like reengineering that we do in medicine,"},{"time":363000,"text":"we just took it straight away, as is."},{"time":365000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":367000,"text":"And so, we launched our own T20 league."},{"time":369000,"text":"Six weeks, city versus city."},{"time":372000,"text":"It was a new thing for us. We had only ever supported our country --"},{"time":374000,"text":"the only two areas in which India was very proud about"},{"time":376000,"text":"their country, representing itself on the field."},{"time":379000,"text":"One was war, the Indian army, which we don't like to happen very often."},{"time":382000,"text":"The other was Indian cricket."},{"time":384000,"text":"Now, suddenly we had to support city leagues."},{"time":387000,"text":"But the people getting into these city leagues"},{"time":390000,"text":"were people who were taking their cues from the West."},{"time":392000,"text":"America is a home of leagues. And they said,"},{"time":394000,"text":"\"Right, we'll build some glitzy leagues here in India.\""},{"time":396000,"text":"But was India ready for it?"},{"time":398000,"text":"Because cricket, for a long time in India was always organized."},{"time":401000,"text":"It was never promoted, it was never sold -- it was organized."},{"time":404000,"text":"And look what they did with our beautiful, nice,"},{"time":407000,"text":"simple family game."},{"time":409000,"text":"All of a sudden, you had that happening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":412000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":429000,"text":"An opening ceremony to match every other."},{"time":431000,"text":"This was an India that was buying Corvettes. This was an India that was buying Jaguar."},{"time":434000,"text":"This was an India that was adding more mobile phones per month"},{"time":437000,"text":"than New Zealand's population twice over."},{"time":439000,"text":"So, it was a different India."},{"time":441000,"text":"But it was also a slightly more orthodox India"},{"time":444000,"text":"that was very happy to be modern,"},{"time":446000,"text":"but didn't want to say that to people."},{"time":449000,"text":"And so, they were aghast when the cheerleaders arrived."},{"time":451000,"text":"Everyone secretly watched them, but everyone claimed not to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":476000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":478000,"text":"The new owners of Indian cricket were not the old princes."},{"time":481000,"text":"They were not bureaucrats who were forced"},{"time":483000,"text":"into sport because they didn't actually love it;"},{"time":485000,"text":"these were people who ran serious companies."},{"time":487000,"text":"And so they started promoting cricket big time,"},{"time":490000,"text":"started promoting clubs big time."},{"time":492000,"text":"And they've started promoting them with huge money behind it."},{"time":495000,"text":"I mean the IPL had 2.3 billion dollars"},{"time":497000,"text":"before a ball was bowled,"},{"time":500000,"text":"1.6 billion dollars for television revenue over 10 years,"},{"time":503000,"text":"and another 70 million dollars plus from all these franchises"},{"time":506000,"text":"that were putting in money. And then they had to appeal to their cities,"},{"time":509000,"text":"but they had to do it like the West, right? Because we are setting up leagues."},{"time":512000,"text":"But what they were very good at doing"},{"time":514000,"text":"was making it very localized."},{"time":518000,"text":"So, just to give you an example of how they did it --"},{"time":520000,"text":"not Manchester United style promotion,"},{"time":522000,"text":"but very Mumbai style promotion. Take a look."}]},{"cues":[{"time":525000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":570000,"text":"Of course, a lot of people said, \"Maybe they dance better than they play.\""},{"time":573000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":575000,"text":"But that's all right. What it did also is it changed the way we looked at cricket."},{"time":579000,"text":"All along, if you wanted a young cricketer,"},{"time":581000,"text":"you picked him up from the bylanes of your own little locality,"},{"time":583000,"text":"your own city, and you were very proud"},{"time":585000,"text":"of the system that produced those cricketers."},{"time":587000,"text":"Now, all of the sudden, if you were to bowl a shot --"},{"time":589000,"text":"if Mumbai were to bowl a shot, for example,"},{"time":592000,"text":"they needn't go to Kalbadevi"},{"time":594000,"text":"or Shivaji Park or somewhere to source them,"},{"time":596000,"text":"they could go to Trinidad."},{"time":598000,"text":"This was the new India, wasn't it? This was the new world,"},{"time":600000,"text":"where you can source from anywhere"},{"time":602000,"text":"as long as you get the best product at the best price."},{"time":604000,"text":"And all of a sudden, Indian sport had awakened to the reality"},{"time":607000,"text":"that you can source the best product for the best price"},{"time":609000,"text":"anywhere in the world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611000,"text":"So, the Mumbai Indians flew in Dwayne Bravo from Trinidad and Tobago,"},{"time":613000,"text":"overnight. And when he had to go back to represent"},{"time":616000,"text":"the West Indies, they asked him, \"When do you have to reach?\""},{"time":620000,"text":"He said, \"I have to be there by a certain time, so I have to leave today.\""},{"time":623000,"text":"We said, \"No, no, no. It's not about when you have to leave;"},{"time":625000,"text":"it's about when do you have to reach there?\""},{"time":628000,"text":"And so he said, \"I've got to reach on date X.\""},{"time":630000,"text":"And they said, \"Fine, you play to date X, minus one.\""},{"time":633000,"text":"So, he played in Hyderabad, went, straight after the game,"},{"time":636000,"text":"went from the stadium to Hyderabad airport,"},{"time":638000,"text":"sat in a private corporate jet -- first refueling in Portugal,"},{"time":641000,"text":"second refueling in Brazil; he was in West Indies in time."},{"time":644000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":645000,"text":"Never would India have thought on this scale before."},{"time":649000,"text":"Never would India have said, \"I want a player to play"},{"time":651000,"text":"one game for me, and I will use a corporate jet"},{"time":654000,"text":"to send him all the way back to Kingston, Jamaica"},{"time":656000,"text":"to play a game.\""},{"time":658000,"text":"And I just thought to myself,"},{"time":660000,"text":"\"Wow, we've arrived somewhere in the world, you know?"},{"time":662000,"text":"We have arrived somewhere. We are thinking big.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":664000,"text":"But what this also did was it started"},{"time":666000,"text":"marrying the two most important things in Indian cricket,"},{"time":668000,"text":"which is cricket and the movies in Indian entertainment."},{"time":671000,"text":"There is cricket and the movies."},{"time":673000,"text":"And they came together because people in the movies"},{"time":675000,"text":"now started owning clubs."},{"time":677000,"text":"And so, people started going to the cricket to watch Preity Zinta."},{"time":681000,"text":"They started going to the cricket to watch Shah Rukh Khan."},{"time":683000,"text":"And something very interesting happened."},{"time":685000,"text":"We started getting song and dance in Indian cricket."},{"time":688000,"text":"And so it started resembling the Indian movies more and more."},{"time":692000,"text":"And of course, if you were on Preity Zinta's team --"},{"time":694000,"text":"as you will see on the clip that follows -- if you did well,"},{"time":696000,"text":"you got a hug from Preity Zinta."},{"time":698000,"text":"So that was the ultimate reason to do well. Take a look --"},{"time":701000,"text":"everyone's watching Preity Zinta."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":721000,"text":"And then of course there was Shah Rukh playing the Kolkata crowd."},{"time":724000,"text":"We'd all seen matches in Kolkata,"},{"time":726000,"text":"but we'd never seen anything like this:"},{"time":728000,"text":"Shah Rukh, with the Bengali song, getting the audiences all worked up"},{"time":731000,"text":"for Kolkata -- not for India, but for Kolkata."},{"time":734000,"text":"But take a look at this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":736000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":752000,"text":"An Indian film star hugging a Pakistani cricketer"},{"time":754000,"text":"because they'd won in Kolkata."},{"time":757000,"text":"Can you imagine?"},{"time":759000,"text":"And do you know what the Pakistani cricketer said?"},{"time":761000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":763000,"text":"\"I wish I was playing for Preity Zinta's team.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":765000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":770000,"text":"But I thought I'd take this opportunity --"},{"time":772000,"text":"there's a few people from Pakistan in here."},{"time":774000,"text":"I'm so happy that you're here"},{"time":776000,"text":"because I think we can show that we can both be together and be friends, right?"},{"time":779000,"text":"We can play cricket together, we can be friends."},{"time":781000,"text":"So thank you very much for coming, all of you from Pakistan."}]},{"cues":[{"time":783000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":787000,"text":"There was criticism too because they said,"},{"time":789000,"text":"\"Players are being bought and sold?"},{"time":791000,"text":"Are they grain?"},{"time":793000,"text":"Are they cattle?\""},{"time":796000,"text":"Because we had this auction, you see."},{"time":798000,"text":"How do you fix a price for a player?"},{"time":801000,"text":"And so the auction that followed"},{"time":803000,"text":"literally had people saying,"},{"time":805000,"text":"\"Bang! so many million dollars for so-and-so player.\""},{"time":808000,"text":"There it is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":810000,"text":"(Music)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":815000,"text":"Auctioneer: Going at 1,500,000 dollars. Chennai."},{"time":822000,"text":"Shane Warne sold for 450,000 dollars."}]},{"cues":[{"time":829000,"text":"HB: Suddenly, a game which earned its players 50 rupees a day --"},{"time":833000,"text":"so 250 rupees for a test match,"},{"time":835000,"text":"but if you finish in four days you only got 200."},{"time":839000,"text":"The best Indian players who played every test match --"},{"time":841000,"text":"every one of the internationals, the top of the line players --"},{"time":843000,"text":"standard contracts are 220,000 dollars in a whole year."},{"time":846000,"text":"Now they were getting 500,000 for six days' work."},{"time":848000,"text":"Then Andrew Flintoff came by from England,"},{"time":850000,"text":"he got one and a half million dollars, and he went back and said,"},{"time":853000,"text":"\"For four weeks, I'm earning more than Frank Lampard and Steven Gerrard,"},{"time":856000,"text":"and I'm earning more than the footballers, wow.\""},{"time":858000,"text":"And where was he earning it from? From a little club in India."},{"time":861000,"text":"Could you have imagined that day would come?"},{"time":864000,"text":"One and a half million dollars for six weeks' work."},{"time":866000,"text":"That's not bad, is it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":870000,"text":"So, at 2.3 billion dollars before the first ball was bowled."},{"time":873000,"text":"What India was doing, though, was benchmarking"},{"time":875000,"text":"itself against the best in the world,"},{"time":877000,"text":"and it became a huge brand."},{"time":879000,"text":"Lalit Modi was on the cover of Business Today."},{"time":881000,"text":"IPL became the biggest brand in India"},{"time":883000,"text":"and, because our elections, had to be moved to South Africa,"},{"time":887000,"text":"and we had to start the tournament in three weeks."},{"time":889000,"text":"Move a whole tournament to South Africa in three weeks."},{"time":891000,"text":"But we did it. You know why?"},{"time":893000,"text":"Because no country works as slowly as we do"},{"time":895000,"text":"till three weeks before an event,"},{"time":897000,"text":"and nobody works fast as we do in the last three weeks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":908000,"text":"Our population, which for a long time we thought was a problem,"},{"time":910000,"text":"suddenly became our biggest asset"},{"time":912000,"text":"because there were more people watching --"},{"time":915000,"text":"the huge consuming class --"},{"time":917000,"text":"everybody came to watch the cricket."},{"time":919000,"text":"We'd also made cricket the only sport in India,"},{"time":922000,"text":"which is a pity, but in India every other sport"},{"time":924000,"text":"pushes cricket to become big,"},{"time":926000,"text":"which is a bit of a tragedy of our times."}]},{"cues":[{"time":928000,"text":"Now, this last minute before I go --"},{"time":930000,"text":"there's a couple of side effects of all this."},{"time":932000,"text":"For a long time, India was this country of poverty,"},{"time":935000,"text":"dust, beggars,"},{"time":938000,"text":"snake charmers, filth,"},{"time":940000,"text":"Delhi belly -- people heard Delhi belly stories before they came."},{"time":943000,"text":"And, all of a sudden, India was this land of opportunity."},{"time":946000,"text":"Cricketers all over the world said,"},{"time":948000,"text":"\"You know, we love India. We love to play in India.\""},{"time":951000,"text":"And that felt good, you know?"},{"time":953000,"text":"We said, \"The dollar's quite powerful actually.\""},{"time":955000,"text":"Can you imagine, you've got the dollar on view"},{"time":957000,"text":"and there's no Delhi belly in there anymore."},{"time":960000,"text":"There's no filth, there's no beggars, all the snake charmers have vanished,"},{"time":963000,"text":"everybody's gone. This tells you how the capitalist world rules."}]},{"cues":[{"time":968000,"text":"Right so, finally,"},{"time":971000,"text":"an English game that India usurped a little bit,"},{"time":975000,"text":"but T20 is going to be the next missionary in the world."},{"time":978000,"text":"If you want to take the game around the world,"},{"time":980000,"text":"it's got to be the shortest form of the game."},{"time":982000,"text":"You can't take a timeless test to China and sit through 14 days with no result in the end,"},{"time":985000,"text":"or you can't take it all over the world."},{"time":987000,"text":"So that's what T20 is doing."},{"time":989000,"text":"Hopefully, it'll make everyone richer, hopefully it'll make the game bigger"},{"time":992000,"text":"and hopefully it'll give cricket commentators more time in the business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":994000,"text":"Thank you very much. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":996000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}